+ * above, tracing back to this exact gap, once data/title.bin's async,
+ * multi-block (2MB+) read was the first case big enough to actually chain
+ * a second callback. Passing `buf`'s own address through here so it's
+ * published before any callback can possibly run closes the gap at its
+ * true root, for both this port and real hardware alike (a strict no-op
